Consumer-side BOM handling
--------------------------

The canonical file is preserved with its UTF-8 BOM (byte sequence
`0xEF 0xBB 0xBF` at offset 0) verbatim from upstream. CoursIA consumers
should read the file as `encoding="utf-8-sig"` (Python) or equivalent
to strip the BOM transparently. Per ai-01 design-gate (msg
`msg-20260703T110001-uqono0`, 2026-07-03), the BOM is part of the
canonical content and must NOT be stripped from the source file.
Any consumer-side compatibility fix belongs in the consumer code,
not in the data file.

